# IAM Concepts Learned

## 1. Policies Define Permissions

AWS IAM policies determine:
- What actions users can perform
- Which services users can access
- Which resources users can use

---

## 2. Missing Permissions Cause Access Denied

If required permissions are missing:
- AWS blocks the action
- Access Denied error is displayed

---

## 3. Different Users Can Have Different Access Levels

AWS IAM allows:
- Service-specific permissions
- Limited user access
- Role-based permission management

---

## 4. Custom Policies Provide Controlled Access

Custom policies help:
- Restrict unnecessary permissions
- Improve security
- Implement least privilege access

---

# Security Concepts Learned

## Principle of Least Privilege

Users should receive:
- Only required permissions
- Limited service access
- Restricted administrative privileges

Purpose:
- Better AWS security management.

---

